nl_problem:
# Task: Nested Logic Test (Depth 5)
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: checkNested(self, x0: int, x1: int, x2: int, x3: int, x4: int) -> bool

# Objective:
This is a test of structural nesting. Return True ONLY if all the following conditions are met:
1. x0 is greater than 0
2. x1 is greater than 0
3. x2 is greater than 0
4. x3 is greater than 0
5. x4 is greater than 0

Each condition must be checked inside the previous one (nested if statements).
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "checkNested")
  (signature ((x0 int) (x1 int) (x2 int) (x3 int) (x4 int)) bool)
  (constraints
    (constraint "All input parameters must be integers.")
    (constraint "The function should return a boolean value indicating whether all conditions are met or not.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "This method checks if all provided integer values are greater than zero, with each condition nested within the previous one. It returns True only if all conditions are satisfied; otherwise, it returns False.")
    (rule "The function should return True if x0 > 0")
    (rule "If x1 is not greater than 0, then stop and return False")
    (rule "If x2 is not greater than 0, then stop and return False")
    (rule "If x3 is not greater than 0, then stop and return False")
    (rule "If x4 is not greater than 0, then stop and return False")
    (return "The function returns True if all conditions are met; otherwise, it returns False.")
  )
)
